## Formatting

### Numbers

- Use numerals for most cases: "3 books"
- Spell out at sentence start: "Three things to know"
- Use comma separators: "1,000 users"

### Dates

- Relative when recent: "2 hours ago", "Yesterday"
- Absolute otherwise: "Jan 9, 2026"

### Lists

- Use bullet points for 3+ items
- End each item consistently (all periods or no periods)
- Keep parallel structure

## Localization

Wegoby supports English (LTR) and Hebrew (RTL).

### Writing for Translation

- Avoid idioms: "Piece of cake" → "Easy to do"
- Don't embed text in images
- Leave room for text expansion (some languages are 30% longer)
- Use Unicode-safe characters

### RTL Considerations

- Icons may need mirroring
- Number direction stays LTR
- Bidirectional text needs care

